            <level1>
                <h1>A simple poem</h1>
                
                <p>Excerpt from Edwin Arlington Robinson's poem The House on the Hill:</p>
                
                <poem>
                    <line>They are all gone away,</line>
                    <line>The House is shut and still,</line>
                    <line>There is nothing more to say.</line>

                    <line>Through broken walls and gray</line>
                    <line>The winds blow bleak and shrill.</line>
                    <line>They are all gone away. </line>
                </poem>

            </level1>
